							<h2 class="title  |  trailer--small">Agricultural Value Chain Guide for the Pacific Islands : Making value chain analysis a useful tool in the hands of farmers, traders and policy makers</h2>
							<p>Published in response to an assessment of the value chain support needs of ACP counties, this guide offers a practical resource on how to analyse and upgrade value chains. Easy to follow and generously illustrated, with numerous full-colour diagrams, charts and photos, the content is deliberately tailored to the needs of those who are actually employed in value chains in the Pacific. As well as an introduction to the topic and a step-by-step guide to value chain analysis, this accessible handbook provides a wealth of lessons from case studies, along with helpful additional tools and resources.</p>
